RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Trial Purse 7200. FOR MAIDENS THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Entry Fee of $250 to be paid on or before time of entry of Trials. Final to be run Sunday, March 12th, 2023. Weights: 3 years old .124 lbs., Older .126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CROSS EXAMINE Trailed lackadaisically along the rail early, prodded with the crop multiple times into the first turn, engaged with rider in move to the backstretch, commenced run at the three-eighths, switched to clear air three wide past the three-sixteenths pole, moved to five path for stretch drive, surged to overtake longtime leader one hundred yards out, finished full of run. BAKERSFIELD BABE Vied inside for the lead into first turn, shrugged off first rival at the three-eighths pole, brushed the other off at the quarter pole, opened up on rivals around bend while shifting to the three path into the stretch, willingly battled but was passed at the sixteenth pole. CLASSIC CALIFORNIA Tracked on inner into first turn sitting behind leading trio, advanced up the rail at the five-sixteenths pole, moved in tandem with eventual winner into the lane, move mitigated by top two down the stretch. DYNAMIC WOMAN Well off the pace opening stages, settled four path in backside run, asked at quarter pole, never fired, only passed tiring. LUCKY LUPE Three wide into first turn, engaged to duel for lead at seven-sixteenths pole, the brief challenge was shrugged off by foe at the quarter pole, gave way, not asked in run to line. WEST COAST ANDY Two wide between while dueling into first turn, struggled to keep pace, retreated at three-eighths pole, not persevered with.

ENTRY.NAME: Classic California
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked inner, adv rail 5/16, moved through str, mitigated

ENTRY.NAME: Cross Examine
ENTRY.COMMENT: Trailed, commenced 3/8 inside, switch 3w turn, surged to victory

ENTRY.NAME: Dynamic Woman
ENTRY.COMMENT: Well off pace early, 4p backside, ask 1/4, never fired

ENTRY.NAME: Bakersfield Babe
ENTRY.COMMENT: Vied early, shrugged off two rivals, opened up, caught 1/16th

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w between first, struggled to keep pace, retreated 3/8ths

ENTRY.NAME: Lucky Lupe
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, engaged duel 7/16, brief challenge 1/4, gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Trial Purse 7200. FOR MAIDENS THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Entry Fee of $250 to be paid on or before time of entry of Trials. Final to be run Sunday, March 12th, 2023. Weights: 3 years old .124 lbs., Older .126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUSTIN'S LADY Assumed lead on rail, always looked a winner, never gave rivals a chance while always keeping them at bay, in hand. SHORT JOURNEY Broke a touch slow but quickly moved up to sit off leader two wide, was no match for leader who stepped away at quarter pole, finished well, clearly second best. SHACKEY'S LOVE Stalked three wide throughout, moved up on turn, no match for winner, outfinished. WITCHES DANCE Tracked in pocket in run to first turn, maintained position to quarter pole, let top trio get away around bend after being set down at the five-sixteenths, moved to the three path for stretch run, hardly a threat. PIRATE MISCHIEF Settled off the pace early in the three path, made a mild move at the three-eighths pole that bore little benefit, three wide into the second turn, never in touch with those who beat him. BELLA VINO Lagged, asked to keep up throughout, always outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Purse 9300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 25, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEFENSE WINS Three wide into the first turn, cleared to the lead at the three-eighths, in command from there to the wire. TIGER BY HIS TAIL Challenged between into the first turn, left to duel for second at the three-eighths pole, two wide into the far turn, outfinished. FIGHT ME Stalked behind top trio into the first turn, commenced move at the quarter pole, swung to the four path for clear air, never threatened down stretch. BREXTON Stumbled at the start, settled off the pace two wide, moved at the quarter pole, sifted through tiring rivals inside for minor honors. LINEMANS CHECK Tracked on rail, never rallied or threatened. BLUE GESSAMI Vied for lead into the first turn, was overtaken by adjoined rival at the three-eighths pole, remained in touch for the minors up to the eighth pole, faded down stretch. ALEX'S GIRL Lept hard at the start and rider did well to remain aboard, hustled up to regain touch with the field, moved up at the seven-sixteenths pole while travelling in the five path to try and make an impact, flattened through lane, unable to make up for tough beginning.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Vied 1st, overtaken 3/8ths, in touch to 1/8, faded

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLD STAR STUDENT Bobbled break but quickly engaged to the lead, never pressured while travelling on rail, coasted. MANY AMBITIONS Three wide into first turn, maintained position between pair of rivals in run up backside, chased after leader after shaking off adjoined foes, moved to rail for drive, a clear second best. ROMEO'S GLORY Taken back along the rail, tracked comfortably off the lead well on the bridle, commenced rally at the five-sixteenths pole, shifted to the three path for the stretch run, gained belatedly. NUMMY NUM Two wide for first turn run, ran in line of three on the backside, packed it in at the quarter pole. PREDETERMINATION Settled four path in rear, passed one tiring rival. ADRIENNE'S PROGENY Four wide first turn, outside of three rivals on backside run, gave way at the five-sixteenths pole.
